Knotted Nets						CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat.Teamwork																																																																																																																						PRETEXT:Exotic Weapon Proficiency (net), base attack bonus +1.																		PRETOTALAB:1							PREWEAPONPROF:1,Net																											DESC:You are capable of entangling far greater prey with the help of your allies.																																																																																																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.11	BENEFIT:If you ready an attack with a net to entangle a creature when an ally of your size who also has this feat attempts to entangle that creature with a net, the two of you can entangle the creature as if you were one size category larger. The entangled creature can attempt to escape both nets as though they were a single net, using the lower of the nets' hit points, hardness (if any), and DCs to break or escape. Only you or your ally can attempt to control the entangled creature's movement with an opposed Strength check, but your ally grants you a +1 bonus on the check. If you work with three other allies of the same size who have this feat, you can entangle a creature as if you were two size categories larger. If you work with seven other allies in this way, you can instead entangle a creature as if you were three size categories larger.
Lovable Scoundrel						CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General																																																																																				PRERACE:1,Tengu,RACESUBTYPE=Tengu					PRESKILL:2,Bluff=1,Diplomacy=1																				PRETEXT:Bluff 1 rank, Diplomacy 1 rank, tengu.																																																												DESC:You're charming enough that others assume your criminal inclinations are delightful quirks.																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.27	BENEFIT:If you fail a Bluff check to deceive, an Intimidate check to gain a target's cooperation, or a Sleight of Hand check to steal from another creature, you can immediately attempt a Diplomacy check against the same DC as a free action. If you succeed, your target assumes your actions were in jest or just some awkward tengu tradition, and its attitude toward you does not immediately worsen (though later actions can still shift its attitude toward hostile). You can use this feat only once per day per target.
Lucky								CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General						PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Black Cat,Lucky Halfling																				PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Halfling ~ Halfling Luck],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Halfling ~ Adaptable Luck],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Catfolk ~ Cat's Luck]																																																				PRETEXT:Black Cat or Lucky Halfling; must have a racial trait with "luck" in its name. A character with the Defiant Luck feat can ignore this feat's prerequisites.																																								DESC:Your luck-based abilities seem limitless.																				ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Lucky Bonus ~ Defiant Luck Choice|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Defiant Luck	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Lucky Bonus ~ Black Cat|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Black Cat	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Lucky Bonus ~ Lucky Halfling|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Lucky Halfling																																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.6	BENEFIT:You gain additional uses of your chosen luck-based feat.
