Rat Stack							CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat.Teamwork					PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Ratfolk ~ Swarming																																																																																																								PRETEXT:Dex 13, swarming racial trait.																									PREVARGTEQ:PreStatScore_DEX,13																															DESC:You coordinate efficiently in tight spaces.																																																																																																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.23	BENEFIT:You can occupy the same square with up to two other creatures that also have this feat. If all participants also have the Tunnel Rat feat, up to four creatures can share the same space.
Rending Swarm						CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat.Teamwork					PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Rat Stack	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Ratfolk ~ Swarming																																																																																																	PRETEXT:Dex 15, Rat Stack, swarming racial trait.																							PREVARGTEQ:PreStatScore_DEX,15																															DESC:Together, you and your allies tear through enemies' defenses.																																																																																																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.23	BENEFIT:You gain a +1 bonus on all melee damage rolls for each allied creature you share a square with that also has this feat. If two or more allies sharing a square have this feat and hit the same adjacent creature in a round, they tear it in different directions, dealing additional damage at the end of the round. This rend attack deals an amount of damage equal to 1d6 + the highest Strength modifier of all qualifying allies in the same square who struck the target this round.
Shapechanging Savage					CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General																																		PREMULT:1,[PREMULT:2,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.ChangeShape],[PRERACE:1,RACESUBTYPE=Shapechanger]],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Wild Shape]	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Improved Feint],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Vigilante Talent ~ Cunning Feint]																																				PRETEXT:Improved Feint or canny feint vigilante talent, change shape ability, shapechanger subtype.																																																			DESC:You catch foes off guard when changing your shape.																																																																																																																												SOURCEPAGE:p.13	BENEFIT:Whenever you use your change shape ability to assume a new form or to return to your true form, you can attempt a Bluff check as a swift action to feint one opponent within 30 feet who witnessed your transformation. You take a -4 penalty on Bluff checks to feint an opponent who is aware that you are a shapechanger. You don't take the usual penalties for feinting a creature of a different type or a creature with an Intelligence score of 1 or 2 when feinting in this manner. [Special] A character with the wild shape class feature counts as having the change shape ability and shapechanger subtype for the purpose of meeting this feat's prerequisites. A character with wild shape can use this feat's benefit whenever she uses wild shape to assume a new form or return to her true form.
Squirming Pile						CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat.Teamwork					PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Ratfolk ~ Swarming																																																																															PRESKILL:1,Acrobatics=5																						PRETEXT:Acrobatics 5 ranks, swarming racial trait.																																																											DESC:Your body is easily lost in the muddy chaos of fighting as a swarm, making your vital areas difficult to target.																																																																																																																		SOURCEPAGE:p.23	BENEFIT:While sharing a square with an ally who has this feat, you gain a 25%% chance of negating the additional damage from a successful critical hit or sneak attack; if you negate the damage, it is instead rolled normally. This negation chance doesn't stack with similar protection provided by any other source, such as the fortification armor special ability.
Startling Shapechange					CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General						PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Dazzling Display																					PREMULT:1,[PREMULT:2,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.ChangeShape],[PRERACE:1,RACESUBTYPE=Shapechanger]],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Wild Shape]																																																										PRETEXT:Dazzling Display, change shape ability, shapechanger subtype.																																																								DESC:You use your shapechanging abilities in order to demoralize your enemies.																																																																																																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.13	BENEFIT:You abruptly change shape, startling those who aren't prepared for your reveal. Whenever you use your change shape ability to assume a new form or return to your true form, you can also use Dazzling Display as a free action. Reduce the result of your Intimidate check by 5 against opponents who know that you are a shapechanger. When using Dazzling Display in this manner, you can use the feat without needing a weapon in hand. [Special] A character with the wild shape class feature counts as having the change shape ability and shapechanger subtype for the purpose of meeting this feat's prerequisites. A character with wild shape can use this feat's benefit whenever she uses wild shape to assume a new form or return to her true form.
Underfoot							CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat							PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Ratfolk ~ Swarming	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Dodge																																																																																																		PRETEXT:Dodge, swarming racial trait.																																								SERVESAS:ABILITY=FEAT|Disruptive																DESC:You clamber in and around your enemies' personal space to devastating effect.																																																																																																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.23	BENEFIT:Benefit: You are able to share a space with a hostile creature at least one size category larger than you. You gain a +2 shield bonus to your AC while occupying an opponent's space, as well as a +2 bonus on all attack rolls against the creature whose space you share. Creatures you share a square with take a -2 penalty on all concentration checks. Entering a space occupied by an opponent provokes an attack of opportunity. This ability does not stack with similar abilities providing a creature benefits for being in another creature's space, such as a mouser swashbuckler's underfoot attack deed. Special: This feat counts as the Disruptive feat for the purpose of qualifying for other feats that have Disruptive as a prerequisite.
Venomous Stare						CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General.Combat.Stare				PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Mesmerist ~ Painful Stare														PRECLASS:1,Mesmerist=11																																																																																						PRETEXT:Mesmerist level 11th, painful stare class feature.																																																										DESC:Your stare is toxic to your enemies.																																																																																																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.17	BENEFIT:When you trigger your painful stare, the target immediately becomes envenomed by the following poison: painful stare-injury; save Fort DC %1; frequency 1/round for 6 rounds; effect 1d3 Dex; cure 2 saves. Whether your target succeeds at or fails its save, you can't use Venomous Stare against that particular foe for 24 hours.|10+(MesmeristLVL/2)+CHA

